  "prompt": "How does the Zika Virus affect men and non pregnant women?",
  "response": "For men and non-pregnant women, Zika virus typically causes mild or no symptoms. Here's a detailed breakdown:\n\nSymptoms (when present):\n- Mild fever\n- Rash\n- Joint pain\n- Conjunctivitis (red eyes)\n- Muscle pain\n- Headache\n\nMost people (80%) experience no symptoms at all.\n\nFor Men:\n- Sexual transmission possible\n- Can potentially cause temporary sexual dysfunction\n- May cause Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome (rare neurological condition)\n- Potential short-term impact on sperm quality\n- Recommended to wait 3-6 months after infection before trying to conceive\n\nFor Non-Pregnant Women:\n- Usually recovers within a week\n- Generally no long-term health consequences\n- Low risk of serious complications\n- Temporary immune response\n- Recommended to avoid pregnancy for several months after infection\n\nPotential Rare Complications:\n- Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome\n- Temporary neurological issues\n- Mild inflammatory conditions\n\nTransmission:\n- Primarily through mosquito bites\n- Possible sexual transmission\n- Can be transmitted from mother to fetus during pregnancy\n\nPrevention:\n- Mosquito bite prevention\n- Safe sex practices\n- Avoiding travel to high-risk areas",
